'California State University, Long Beach' (also known as 'Cal State Long Beach',
'Long Beach State', 'CSULB', 'LBSU', or 'The Beach') is the second largest
campus of the 23 school California State University system (CSU) and one of the largest universities in the state of
California by enrollment, its student body numbering 36,279 for the Fall 2012
semester. At 5,148 students, the university enrolls one of the largest graduate
student populations across the CSU and in the state of California alone. http://www.calstate.edu/as/stat_reports/2012-
2013/f12_01.htm The university is located at the southeastern coastal tip
of Los Angeles County, less than one mile from the border with Orange County. [http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&hl=en&q=W+Campus+Dr+%26+E+State+University+-
Dr,+Long+Beach,+CA+90840&ie=UTF8&om=1 Map] The university offers 137
different Bachelor's degrees, 92 types of Master's degrees, 5 Doctoral degrees
including two Doctor of Education, a Ph.D in Engineering, a Doctor of Physical
Therapy and Education specialist, and 29 different teaching credentials. ht-
tp://degrees.calstate.edu/csu_degree_search2?noCache=126:1358365975 h-
ttp://degrees.calstate.edu/uploads/55/64/5564d4b6ec1584227ca2d1054c759f0f/Crede-
ntial-Programs-08212012.pdf

Long Beach State is one of the West Coast's top universities in student body
racial diversity, being named the 5th most diverse university in the West by
U.S. News & World Report. [http://www.csulb.edu/misc/beach-
review/archives/2007/fall/noteworthy/ CSULB Receives High Rankings] Retrieved
February 18, 2009 [http://cf.papubs.csulb.edu/news-
events/story.cfm?hackid=1418 This Week @ The Beach] Retrieved August 18,
2010 It is also home to the largest publicly funded art school west of the
Mississippi. The university currently operates with one of the lowest student
fees in the country at US$6,738 per year for full-time students having
California residence. [http://www.csulb.edu/depts/enrollment/re-
gistration/fees_basics.html Fees and Finances â Basics]. Division of
Administration & Finance. Retrieved July 8, 2009 Resultantly, CSULB has
been recognized repeatedly as one of "America's Best Value Colleges" by the
